&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp An awkward silence followed, no one was quite sure of what to do. The king was standing, with his hand still up, opening and closing his mouth, like he was trying to think of something to say but his brain wasn't functioning. Or, to be more precise, like a fish in a tank, opening and closing its mouth not doing a thing. Trent was slumping low into his chair, giving happy looks to Jade, while looking around giving apologetic looks to everyone else as his face turned a dark shade of crimson. The rest were looking back and forth, unsure of what to do next. Kennith broke the silence by standing and asking,<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Can I continue, or are there going to be anymore interruptions?&quot;<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp With that the king stopped trying to think of a response to Jade. He sat down heavily into his chair and waved unenthusiastically to Kennith.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Yes, whatever, get on with it,&quot; was the best thing he could muster.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Kennith cleared his throat, he gave a last look around the room, as if to see if their was anyone else ready to jump out of the shadows throwing knives. After assuring himself that there was not he started talking again.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Correct me if I'm wrong but I believe the last thing I said before I was interrupted was that The other way to defeat the undead is we send a team to take out 현i- Ythert鴻 and Gostmaster.&quot;<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp He looked around the hall for conformation, there were a few nods of recognition and a few mumbles of agreement. Satisfied with this Kennith went back to talking.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Now the concern was raised, 'What will happen after?'&quot;<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Again he looked around the hall. Jarlin nodded.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;When we kill those two, the undead army will die. The magic holding them together will fail and there bodies will become inanimate corpses again. Then all we have to worry about is the new evil. But as history has taught us we will never be rid of the new evil. Every time this happens the new evil stays. It can be thinned down to a small annoyance. The problem is, every time this happens the evils join up with the new evil. So unless we can find the original source, they will grow stronger every fourteen hundred years . We may beat them now, but eventually we will fall.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp But this is not a concern for now. The concerns for now is defeating Gostmaster and 현i- Ythert鴻, not letting the undead cross the Krackaiden, finding the new evil, creating our alliance and finding the power sources.&quot;<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Oh, is that all?&quot; laughed Trent, &quot; I thought we might have a hard job, we should have that done in time for tea.&quot;<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Jarlin started to chuckle, soon Grunsfoot joined in, then Shade, The Elves, Shade and before long the entire council was roaring with laughter. Tellurian stood up and shushed them.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I'm glad to see we are all in such high spirits, but for tonight I would suggest we all go to bed, we will reconvene in the morning to discuss military tactics.&quot;<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Trent sighed to himself at this news, after this meeting the last thing he wanted was another so soon, he hoped that it wouldn't be as formal as this one, maybe even outside! He made a mental note to suggest that.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp With that the council was dismissed and most of them did just that. Except for Trent, Shade, Kennith and Jade, who walked into the courtyard, sat under a tree, and began to talk.<br>
